{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe live Jira/LLM external tier (`tests/external/`) runs only on `workflow_dispatch`\n(`.github/workflows/external-integration.yml`), which sets `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1` and maps\n`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`/`OPENAI_API_KEY` but **no `JIRA_*` secrets** — so the Jira round-trip test\n(`tests/external/test_link_sync_roundtrip_live.py`) can only ever SKIP, and Jira API/SDK drift\nmerges through normal CI with no real integration signal. And nothing fails a run in which the\nwhole external tier silently skips. VALIDATED.\n\n## What\n1. **Schedule + wire Jira secrets** (`external-integration.yml`): add an `on.schedule` cron\n   trigger (weekly) alongside `workflow_dispatch`, and map `JIRA_URL` / `JIRA_USER` /\n   `JIRA_API_TOKEN` from `secrets.*` into the external job's env (so the live Jira test can\n   authenticate when the secrets are configured). Keep it non-destructive: the live test\n   targets a read-only / uniquely-tagged project (no mass mutation).\n2. **Fail-on-all-skip canary** (`tests/external/conftest.py`): add a pytest session hook that,\n   when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is truthy (a real scheduled/dispatch run), REPORTS the\n   executed-vs-skipped counts for the external tier and FAILS the session if EVERY external\n   test skipped (zero executed) — turning a credential-less/all-skip run RED instead of a\n   false green, so drift is surfaced. When `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is not set (the default suite,\n   where the tier is intentionally inert), the hook is a no-op.\n3. **Tests** for the canary logic and the workflow wiring:\n   - a unit test of the fail-on-all-skip hook: simulate an all-skipped external session with\n     `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1` and assert the hook signals failure; simulate ≥1 executed and\n     assert it passes; and assert it is inert when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset.\n   - a config-as-artifact test asserting `external-integration.yml` declares an `on.schedule`\n     trigger AND maps `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/`JIRA_API_TOKEN` into the external job env (a\n     drift guard on the workflow, mirroring the repo's other YAML-artifact tests).\n\n## Scope\n- `.github/workflows/external-integration.yml` — schedule trigger + JIRA_* env mapping.\n- `tests/external/conftest.py` — fail-on-all-skip session hook + executed/skipped report.\n- A test module (e.g. `tests/unit/test_external_canary.py`) for the hook + workflow wiring.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The workflow declares an `on.schedule` trigger and maps `JIRA_URL`/`JIRA_USER`/\n      `JIRA_API_TOKEN` from secrets into the external job env; a config-as-artifact test pins\n      this wiring.\n- [ ] The conftest fails an external session in which every external test skipped (with\n      `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL=1`), and is a no-op when `REBAR_RUN_EXTERNAL` is unset — asserted by\n      a behavioral test of the hook.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The `JIRA_URL` / `JIRA_USER` / `JIRA_API_TOKEN` repository secrets are\n      configured in the GitHub repo settings so the scheduled canary actually exercises the live\n      Jira path (this requires GitHub repo-admin access to set the secrets; it cannot be done\n      from the code change and is attested by the operator with the secret-config evidence).\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783807151614547001,"uuid":"8dae9c86-cf22-4e80-bf6e-6c4c43428953"}